Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have attracted significant attention as a highly efficient type of fuel cell.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Recent research proposes the use of co-doped scandium-stabilized zirconia with Gd and Ce (denoted as 10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ) and Yb and Bi co-doped gadolinium-doped ceria (denoted as GYBC) as promising materials for the electrolyte and buffer layers, respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: 10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ exhibits excellent structural stability and ionic conductivity, which can be attributed to the doping of Ce for enhanced stability and Gd for improved ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: On the other hand, GYBC demonstrates good sinterability and ionic conductivity due to the ability of Bi to lower the sintering temperature and the high ionic conductivity of Yb.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To evaluate the feasibility of 10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ and GYBC at the single cell level.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) peaks and Rietveld refinements show good structural stability with slight increase in the lattice parameter by doping.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The particle morphologies, size distributions, and BET surface areas are evaluated for the basic material characterizations.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Then, lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF)-gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) was selected as cathode material with 10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ and GYBC.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Finally, a single cell composed of Ni-Yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ)/10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ/GYBC/LSCF-GDC (6.5:3.5) is fabricated by sequential 3-layer co-tape casting technique, and it shows good open circuit voltage of > 1.0 V, high electrochemical performance of 0.73 W/cm2 and low ohmic resistance of 0.17 Omega cm(2) at 750 C-degrees.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Then, the electrochemical characteristics and long-term durability of this single cell are evaluated over 500 h without degradation issues.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Based on these results, it is concluded that 10Sc0.5Gd0.5CeSZ and GYBC are promising candidate materials for SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of Electrolyte Materials of Gd- and Ce-Doped Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia and Yb- and Bi-Doped Gadolinium-Doped Ceria for Highly Durable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
